        {
      "pitch": -14.1,
      "yaw": -25.1,
      "type": "info",
      "text": "<div class='tarjeta-museo' style='width: 650px; padding: 20px;'> <div class='tarjeta-info' style='display: flex; gap: 30px;'> <div style='flex: 1;'> <h3 style='color: var(--color-primario-oscuro); border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-secundario); display: inline-block; padding-bottom: 5px; margin-bottom: 10px;'>Xochiquetzal</h3> <p style='font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5; color: #444;'>Escultura a la deidad <em>Xochiquetzal</em>, labrada en roca volcánica y hallada en la Acrópolis de Xochicalco.<br><br>El personaje, de sexo indefinido, está sentado en posición de sumisión y adornado con plumas que representan lo precioso en Mesoamérica. Presenta símbolos de movimiento y caracoles cortados, similares a los del Templo de las Serpientes Emplumadas.<br><br>Pesa unos 1600 kilos y es conocida localmente como <em>La Malinche</em>.</p> </div> <div style='flex: 1; border-left: 1px solid #ccc; padding-left: 20px;'> <h3 style='color: var(--color-secundario); border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-primario); display: inline-block; padding-bottom: 5px; margin-bottom: 10px;'>Xochiquetzal</h3> <p style='font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5; color: #444;'>Sculpture of the deity <em>Xochiquetzal</em>, carved in volcanic rock and found in the Acropolis of Xochicalco.<br><br>The character, of unidentified sex, is seated in a position of submission and adorned with feathers representing preciousness in Mesoamerica. It features cut shells and movement symbols similar to those in the Temple of the Feathered Serpents.<br><br>Weighing around 3520 pounds, this deity is locally known as <em>La Malinche</em>.</p> </div> </div> </div>"
